Dio - San Jose KBFH Metal 1983 ak192

Dio was an American heavy metal band from Cortland, New York. Formed in October 1982 by eponymous vocalist Ronnie James Dio and drummer Vinny Appice following their departure from Black Sabbath, the original lineup of the group also included guitarist Vivian Campbell and bassist Jimmy Bain. After the release of Holy Diver in 1983 It was on and cracken...

Meanwhile...
King Biscuit was busy here in the Silicon valley They had just grabbed Queensryche  for a short show and now Dio out Supporting The Holy Diver album 
Sounding as good as he would ever be at the best time. 
Holy Diver and Than The Last in Line and Sacred Heart . 

Good Times.  

Reagan was in the White house and his Economic idea was booming. 
Even the homeless had wads of cash and bindles of Coke.  
The ride was gonna roll for the next 5 - 6 years.
